  "title": "partialUpdateObject is not a function",
  "body": "I'm going to use partialUpdateObject for updating one attribute by ObjectID.\r\nBut not working.\r\n\"TypeError: index.partialUpdateObject is not a function\" is occured.\r\nBut index.search is working.\r\nFollowing code shows my code.\r\nJS:\r\n```js\r\nconst client = algoliasearch(API_ID, AdminAPIKey);\r\n\r\n  // 1. Initialize the target and temporary indices\r\n  const index = client.initIndex(INDEXNAME);\r\n\r\nindex.search({ query: 'query string' }, (err, content) => {\r\n  if (err) {\r\n    console.log(err);\r\n    console.log(err.debugData);\r\n    return;\r\n  }\r\n  console.log(content.hits);\r\n});\r\n\r\nindex.partialUpdateObject({\r\n  test_attribute: 'testvalue',\r\n  objectID: 'XXX'\r\n}, function (err, content) {\r\n  if (err) throw err;\r\n\r\n  console.log(content);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nHTML:\r\n```html\r\n    <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/algoliasearch@3.32.0/dist/algoliasearchLite.min.js\"></script>\r\n    <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@3.0.0\"></script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat do I have to do for partialUpdateObject?\r\nDo I have to run following npm commands? If then, where do I have to run?\r\n```\r\nnpm install --save algoliasearch\r\nnpm install --save-dev @types/algoliasearch\r\n```\r\n\r\nThank you.",
